        <td bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top' width='100%'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'><font face=Verdana><BR>So, after debating to myself for a couple levels while I was in Oasis whether to make the trek to Kurn's Tower, which I'd heard was nice (I didn't know much about it, as this is my first character), at lvl 15 I picked up most of my lvl 16 spells in Freeport, and headed off.</P><P>Sure, I had to wait like 40 minutes for the boat in TD (I think I'd just missed it), and cross Overthere and Warsliks Woods (and cross back over them to bank), but it really, truly, honestly is worth it :) It's just like candy =D</P><P>I soloed the first floor room that's to the right after the entrance -- works great because you can park your pet and med behind the wall, and pull at your leisure, with very few interruptions. Tonight I started poking around downstairs a bit. Maybe in levelling to 19 or 20 I'll pick up an uber soloist's wand or IBC to sell (I wouldn't want to spend the very uber amount of time it would take me to specifically camp them (especially if someone else wants to), I'll just be happy if I'm uber lucky ;P ). (At 19 or 20 I'll probably head up to SK to find those Treants I've heard so much about). In general Kurn's is a really nice place, and most of the time you'll practically have it all to yourself. So, if any fellow n00bs are reading this, definitely consider taking your necro here, even if you're from way over in Paineel like me. :) And I've only died once, hooray!</P><P>Course, it seems like most of you people hanging out here are 40+.. this message won't seem very interesting to you guys. But I enjoy reading this board.. I'm coming to love my necro. (it's not my very first character, but the first one I really got into, and got past level 7) I happy. :) Back to lurking now.</P><P>-ni</P><P><BR></font id=Verdana></P><P> </font></td>
